Ernest Borisovich Vinberg (Russian: Эрнест Борисович Винберг; born 26 July 1937) is a Russian mathematician, who works on discrete subgroups of Lie groups and representation theory. He introduced Vinberg's algorithm and the Koecher–Vinberg theorem. He is a recipient of the Humboldt Prize.   == References == Ernest Vinberg at the Mathematics Genealogy Project Humboldt Research Award. Ernest Borisovich Vinberg, Moscow Mathematical Journal
